rom the women’s vision foundation  and  recognized by the united states environmental protection agency as a leading company supporting renewable generation capacity   and  “top  military friendly employers” according to gi jobs  and  military times edge “best for vets”  controversiesedit department of justice lawsuitedit in october  the us department of justice announced that davita agreed to pay the government  million to settle a false claims act lawsuit that alleged that davita paid kickbacks to receive referrals of patients to its dialysis clinics davita agreed to pay another  million in a civil forfeiture related to two specific joint ventures in denver as part of the settlement davita was required to divest itself of joint ventures and submit to monitoring the lawsuit alleged that for almost a decade davita sought out doctors with a large number of patients with renal disease and offered lucrative joint venture opportunities violating the state and federal false claims act and the federal antikickback statute a whistleblower qui tam lawsuit was brought by david barbetta a former davita employee the whistleblower lawsuit which was filed in  remained under seal for more than three years while the government reviewed the claims in april  us attorney sally yates informed the parties that the government had declined to join the case the lawsuit alleges that the protocol for zemplar allowed for only  mg vials of the vitamin d supplement to be used when the prescribed dose was  mg or less but if the prescribed dose was  mg for example a  mg vial — not three  mg vials — was to be used with  mg being wasted the suit said the suit said if davita followed certain sterilization safeguards the unused medication in the venofer vials could be used for other patients the company followed such procedures when using the far more expensive drug epogen during much of the same time the suit said in a statement davita acknowledged that such a practice — called reentry — was allowed as an option to healthcare providers by the government between  and  but since  the centers for disease control and prevention and the centers for medicare and medicaid services have banned it the agencies have warned that any potential cost savings from allowing multiple syringe draws from a single vial are outweighed by the possible risk of infection on november   cnn health ran a story about accusations of large scale medicaremedicaid fraud made against davita dialysis insurance steeringedit in october  the st louis post dispatch reported that davita had been steering low income dialysis patients to purchase unneeded private medical insurance patients were told their private insurance premiums would be subsidized by the american kidney fund at no cost to the patient while providing the same service dialysis covered by private insurance is much more profitable for davita due to lower rates of reimbursement from medicare and medicaid the american kidney fund subsequently introduced new measures to ensure patients applying for support truly need private insurance rather than using medicare or medicaid see alsoedit colorado portal companies portal kimberly clark saenz referencesedit  a b c d e f davita form k annual report filing date mar   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved mar     chuang tamara  may  davita will pay  million to settle atlanta whistleblower case denver post retrieved  june    davita form q quarterly report filing date nov   secdatabasecom retrieved mar     davita form k current report filing date oct   secdatabasecom retrieved mar     kent thiry and davita leadership challenges in building and growing a great company permanent dead link  davita dva fortune retrieved  march    davita form k current report filing date dec   secdatabasecom retrieved mar     davita inc  company profile information business description history background information   davita form k annual report filing date feb   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved mar     times los angeles  health