oss th street from the current headquarters groundbreaking for  chestnut occurred in june  with a completion anticipated for mid to late  corporate social responsibilityedit sustainabilityedit davita has initiated several sustainability programs to reduce the company footprint and was the only kidney care company recognized by the united states environmental protection agency for its sustainability initiatives in  davita opened the first leedcertified dialysis center in the us and is currently seeking leed gold certification for its new headquarters being built in denver in  davita installed solar thermal technology as a trial at one facility in scottsburg indiana initial analysis of the trial showed a  percent reduction in natural gas consumption versus comparable davita facilities in the region dialyzer components are made entirely from crude oil and the nondegradable parts comprise more than  million pounds of medical waste annually though dialyzer reuse has sparked a controversy in the dialysis industry davita continues to allow patients to choose either singleuse dialyzers or reuse which is estimated to save  million pounds of medical waste annually davita also launched a dialyzer recycling pilot with waste management inc and becton dickinson believed to be the first program of this type community outreachedit davita works in conjunction with many organizations to raise awareness of chronic kidney disease davita has supported the kidney trust to provide more than  kidney screenings as part of the kidney trust’s ckd rapidtesting program the early detection of kidney disease can delay the onset of dialysis and improve the quality of life for patients davita kidney rockedit the davita kidney rock is a k run walk event that raises awareness of chronic kidney disease and funds in support of this cause the  davita kidney rock was held in denver’s city park and featured complimentary kidney disease screenings for participants by the kidney trust a health fair and games and prizes in the kids zone tour davitaedit tour davita is an annual threeday mile bike ride to raise awareness of and funds for the fight against kidney disease the fifth annual tour davita was held sept  – sept  in massachusetts new york and connecticut in  tour davita raised  for the kidney trust village service daysedit davita teammates engage in village service days by making a positive difference in their local communities village service days include volunteer activities where davita teammates support the work of various local c nonprofit organizations the kidney trustedit the kidney trust was founded in  by davita it is an independent nonprofit organization that believes everyone should be empowered to take a proactive role in their health the kidney trust is seeking to reduce the progression of chronic kidney disease ckd through free rapid screening in nonmedical settings and providing financial assistance to people affected bridge of life  davita medical missionsedit bridge of life—davita medical missions is a c nonprofit organization founded by davita that provides treatment education and care to ckd patients in developing countries bridge of life has completed  missions bringing dialysis services to cameroon india ecuador guatemala and the philippines awards and rankingsedit – fortune magazine’s “world’s most admired companies”  ranked number  on the fortune   debuted at number  on informationweek  list  colorado biz “top company in health care” – “best companies to work for in colorado” among the  best large companies those with  employees by colorado biz  named one of denver business journal’s “best places to work” – “top ” ranked companies of employersponsored workforce training and development by training magazine – davita chairman and ceo kent thiry named one of the “ most powerful people in healthcare” by modern healthcare – ranked among worldblu “most democratic workplaces” – top  in  and top  in  in the environmental ranking of the  largest publicly traded companies in america by newsweek  “corporate vision award” from the women’s vision foundation  and  recognized by the united states environmental protection agency as a leading company supporting renewable generation capacity   and  “top  military friendly employers” according to gi jobs  and  military times edge “best for vets”  controversiesedit department of justice lawsuitedit in october  the us department of justice announced that davita agreed to pay the government  million to settle a false claims act lawsuit that alleged that davita paid kickbacks to receive referrals of patients to its dialysis clinics davita agreed to pay another  million in a civil forfeiture related to two specific joint ventures in denver as part of the settlement davita was required to divest itself of joint ventures and submit to monitoring the lawsuit alleged that for almost a decade davita sought out doctors with a large number of patients with renal disease and offered lucrative joint venture opportunities violating the state and federal false claims act and the federal antikickback statute a whistleblower qui tam lawsuit was brought by david barbetta a former davita employee the whistleblower lawsuit which was filed in  remained under seal for more than three years while the government reviewed the claims in april  us attorney sally yates informed the parties that the government had declined to join the case the lawsuit alleges that the protocol for zemplar allowed for only  mg vials of the vitamin d supplement to be used when the prescribed dose was  mg or less but if the prescribed dose was  mg for example a  mg vial — not three  mg vials — was to be used with  mg being wasted the suit said the suit said if davita followed certain sterilization safeguards the unused medication in the venofer vials could be used for other patients the company followed such procedures when using the far more expensive drug epogen during much of the same time the suit said in a statement davita acknowledged that such a practice — called reentry — was allowed as an option to healthcare providers by the government between  and  but since  the centers for disease control and prevention and the centers for medicare and medicaid services have banned it the agencies have warned that any potential cost savings from allowing multiple syringe draws from a single vial are outweighed by the possible risk of infection on november   cnn health ran a story about accusations of large scale medicaremedicaid fraud made against davita dialysis insurance steeringedit in october  the st louis post dispatch reported that davita had been steering low income dialysis patients to purchase unneeded private medical insurance patients were told their private insurance premiums would be subsidized by the american kidney fund at no cost to the patient while providing the same service dialysis covered by private insurance is much more profitable for davita due to lower rates of reimbursement from medicare and medicaid the american kidney fund subsequently introduced new measures to ensure patients applying for support truly need private insurance rather than using medicare or medicaid see alsoedit colorado portal companies portal kimberly clark saenz referencesedit  a b c d e f davita form k annual report filing date mar   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved mar     chuang tamara  may  davita will pay  million to settle atlanta whistleblower case denver post retrieved  june    davita form q quarterly report filing date nov   secdatabasecom retrieved mar     davita form k current report filing date oct   secdatabasecom retrieved mar     kent thiry and davita leadership challenges in building and growing a great company permanent dead link  davita dva fortune retrieved  march    davita form k current report filing date dec   secdatabasecom retrieved mar     davita inc  company profile information business description history background information   davita form k annual report filing 